{"id": "byyowy", "title": "If you already are holding 100 or more BYND stock here's what you need to do", "selftext": "Sell your stock.\n\nSell puts = to shares sold/100.\n\nBuy a call same strike.\n\nHold onto the proceeds to cover your put.\n\nIf the stock goes to zero you locked in the put proceeds. Way better than holding shares.\n\nIf the stock goes to 1,000 your calls are covering your upside just as well as your shares would have.\n\nIf the stock goes nowhere you made huge put premiums instead of nothing.\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nExample. 100 shares. Sell jan 2020 atm put for 8,000. Sell shares for 17,500. 25,500 proceeds. Buy atm call for 3000, same duration. Net 22,500.\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nStock goes to 0. Put costs you 17,500. +5000 on if you just held shares.\n\nStock doesn't move, everything expires worthless +5000 on if you just held shares.\n\nStock goes to 1000. Calls worth 82,000 plus 22,500 from sale of stock and puts &gt; 100,000 from holding shares alone.\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nThis also works if you can borrow the stock sufficiently cheaply but good luck with that one.", "created_utc": 1560177855, "permalink": "/r/wallstreetbets/comments/byyowy/if_you_already_are_holding_100_or_more_bynd_stock/", "is_self": true}